# Window OS GUI - Title Bar API Documentation

The `window.os.gui.titleBar` is a JavaScript function that creates a customizable title bar for a GUI application. It takes three parameters: `title` (string), `buttonClickCallback` (function), and `parentElement` (DOM element). 

## Parameters

### title (string)
The title to be displayed on the title bar. This is a required parameter and should be a string.

### buttonClickCallback (function)
This is a callback function that will be executed when the close button is clicked. This is also a required parameter and should be a function that takes no arguments and does not return a value.

### parentElement (DOM element)
This is the DOM element that the title bar will be appended to. This is also a required parameter and should be a valid DOM element (e.g., a div or a section).

## Usage
```javascript
// Assuming you have a div with id 'app' in your HTML file
var appDiv = document.getElementById('app');

// Define your callback function
var closeApp = function() {
    // Your code to close the application goes here
};

// Create a title bar with the title 'My App' and the closeApp callback
window.os.gui.titleBar('My App', closeApp, appDiv);

```
